(390, 3, '2013-10-16 13:13:37', '2013-10-16 11:13:37', 'At OIM we understand that the strategic planning and thinking process isn’t a once-off event. If you want to remain current and competitive you need continuous review and alignment.\r\n\r\nWe partner with organisations to help facilitate and establish this process. The outcome is:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>A well-planned strategy</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Informed by sound research and debate.</li>\r\n	<li>With clearly articulated implementation plans.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Internal capability</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A method for ongoing reviews.</li>\r\n	<li>A database that guides decision making.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Execution methodology</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To ensure everyone in the organisations is engaged and focused on the performance goals and plays their part in strategy execution.</li>\r\n	<li>Relevant tools for communication and strategy implementation, eg business and functional scorecards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>OUR OFFERING</h2>\r\n<strong>OIM can facilitate:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A comprehensive strategic planning intervention spanning about three months.</li>\r\n	<li>A one- or two-day workshop to re-focus priorities and action plans.</li>\r\n	<li>Regular strategic reviews and updates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>THE OIM DIFFERENCE</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We do not believe in consultant dependency. Therefore sustainability, inclusivity and building internal capacity for the design, implementation and execution of strategy are key elements in our process.</li>\r\n	<li>An inherent part of this approach is the establishment of a framework for ongoing reviews.</li>\r\n	<li>We have successfully facilitated strategic planning interventions for a range of clients, many of whom still rely on our expertise to help facilitate workshops or interventions at critical junctures in their business journey.</li>\r\n	<li>OIM has also been leaders in the field of employee engagement (INVOCOM®) since the early 80s with implementation in a range of industries and countries. INVOCOM® is the execution methodology we establish at organisations as part of the strategic planning offering.</li>\r\n	<li>If required, clients also have access to the expertise embedded in the rest of OIM’s specialist areas, namely organisational performance improvement, operational optimisation and people management.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Strategic Planning', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '385-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-16 13:13:37', '2013-10-16 11:13:37', '', 385, 'http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/news/uncategorized/385-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(392, 3, '2013-10-16 13:25:29', '2013-10-16 11:25:29', 'Communication is the golden thread that runs through the implementation of any organisational strategy or change initiative. It ties everything together from start to finish and ensure clarity among all.\r\n\r\nCommunication’s ultimate success, however, is closely linked to two aspects:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alignment with your business strategy.</li>\r\n	<li>Effective employee engagement to share information, create understanding and effect mindset change to acquire the subsequent behaviour and culture change.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur approach to strategic and change communication addresses these two crucial aspects.\r\n<h2>OUR OFFERING</h2>\r\nWe provide a unique approach to communication that engages employees, namely:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Information sharing and awareness:</strong> Using a range of communication tools, eg social networking, road shows, newsletters, posters and communication campaigns.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Peer-to-peer influence:</strong> Establish change champions and peer-level leaders who share information, create buy-in and influence on an informal level.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Business understanding:</strong> Coupled with information sharing and peer champions, we use OIM’s Climate Creation Workshops to ensure all employees have a holistic understanding of the business context and how their role contributes to organisational success. Similarly, OIM’s employee engagement methodology, <a href="http://www.oimgroup.com/products-services/people-management/employee-engagement/">INVOCOMS®</a>, is used to engage teams around business goals, team conduct and specific focused communication and learning topics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>The integration of these elements results in an informed, engaged workforce that is motivated to be part of the unfolding change within the organisation.</strong>\r\n\r\nBelow is an overview of the main offerings that work in partnership to provide this unique approach.\r\n\r\n<strong>A. Strategic communication</strong>\r\nAim: A clearly defined strategic plan to influence stakeholders positively through communication\r\n\r\nTraditional strategic communication uses a hierarchical method of information sharing. This is done in a variety of ways such as presentations, workshops and electronic communication. While information sharing is important, it often lacks engagement, tends to create the impression of “being spoken to”, and commonly does not direct the right message in the right way to the right people. To address these shortcomings, OIM In Context establishes a clearly defined communication framework based on the following key elements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Stakeholder analysis</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Communication climate check</strong> (by means of survey tools)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Key message development</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Key message delivery</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>B. Change communication</strong>\r\nAim: Support new business initiatives through a change communication plan that accurately informs people of the upcoming change, creates understanding around it and establishes buy-in. <strong>Change communication plays a crucial role in any change initiative and is an important key to sustainable behavioural and culture change.</strong>\r\n\r\nOur offering comprises the following elements:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Change readiness assessment</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Stakeholder map and key message design</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Informal social network</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Peer-to-peer influence: </strong>People are influenced by what they see and behaviours are copied. Therefore we train change champions and peer-level leaders.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll the above elements are supported by consultation and training to ensure the full understanding, involvement and cooperation of employees.\r\n<h2>THE OIM IN CONTEXT DIFFERENCE</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We are focused on providing <strong>practical solutions</strong> to deliver results.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>We partner with our clients</strong> to develop plans that are relevant and focused.</li>\r\n	<li>The offering <strong>seamlessly integrates</strong> with other OIM products and services.</li>\r\n	<li>We ensure stakeholder engagement from the start to the end of the process.</li>\r\n	<li>We pride ourselves in being flexible, always adapting to client’s strategic needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Our services are available to small, medium and large organisations.</li>\r\n	<li>We have access to a local and international network of virtual specialists to draw on relevant expertise when required.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>We move fast and ensure everyone has fun along the way!</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOIM’s strategic and change communication offerings are offered in partnership with niche\r\nconsulting company <a href="http://www.incontext.co.za/" target="_blank">In Context</a>.', 'Strategic and Change Communication', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'strategic-and-change-communication', '', '', '2014-05-21 12:34:19', '2014-05-21 10:34:19', '', 0, 'http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=products_services&#038;p=392', 0, 'products_services', '', 0),
