cesses and standard operating procedures (SOPs)...<a title="Operations Management Interventions" href="http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/products-services/organisational-development/operations-management-interventions-2/">Read more</a></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Business systems:</strong> We project manage the implementation of IT systems to meet your business architecture requirements...<a title="IT Systems" href="http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/products-services/operations-management/information-technology-management/">Read more</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>THE OIM DIFFERENCE</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>OIM’s offering is unique in that we have a multidisciplinary team of consultants with decades of experience in operations management, organisational performance and people management.</strong></li>\r\n	<li>This offers seamless integration of the following key areas that relate to your business architecture:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strategic planning</li>\r\n	<li>Organisational and operational structures</li>\r\n	<li>Scorecards</li>\r\n	<li>Processes and productivity standards</li>\r\n	<li>Project management of information systems</li>\r\n	<li>Competency profiling</li>\r\n	<li>Reward strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Change management and change communication</li>\r\n	<li>Individual performance management</li>\r\n	<li>Operational communication structures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Business Architecture', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '412-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-18 14:07:25', '2013-10-18 12:07:25', '', 412, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/news/uncategorized/412-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(709, 3, '2013-10-18 14:22:13', '2013-10-18 12:22:13', 'Scorecards play a crucial role in organisational, team and individual performance management. They are used to translate strategic priorities to all organisational levels to establish overall alignment and a collective focus on the right goals and targets.\n\nUsing a structured approach, OIM''s scorecard development process aligns functional and team performance to the business strategy and standard operational areas. We clearly define goals and targets and cascade them throughout the business to accurately reflect level and content of work. This ensures that all functions add value to the business based on a common understanding of the organisational goals.\n\nWe also train staff in the use of scorecards and the contracting of performance.\n<h2>OUR OFFERING</h2>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Consultation and scorecard design:</strong> Managing and facilitating the scorecard process. This includes reaching agreement on design principles, templates, roll-out method and timelines. An inclusive approach is adopted when designing the scorecards to generate a sense of ownership and buy-in among line managers.</li>\n	<li><strong>Training:</strong> Equipping leaders with the necessary skills to design and manage scorecards and agree on a performance contract with teams/individuals.</li>\n	<li><strong>Toolkit:</strong> Designing and customising a toolkit for ease of implementation, eg templates and user guides.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>The link with strategy, operational goals and individual performance</strong>\n\nScorecards are the tool that links strategy with operational goals as well as team and individual performance. OIM has the expertise to assist clients with strategic planning, developing operational scorecards, setting up teams to manage their <a title="Employee engagement (INVOCOMS)" href="http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/products-services/people-management/employee-engagement-invocoms/">own performance</a> and <a href="http://www.oimgroup.com/products-services/people-management/talent-management/performance-management-process.php">individual performance</a>, allowing for a seamless integration of the scorecard process with performance.\n<h2>THE OIM DIFFERENCE</h2>\n<ul>\n	<li>OIM''s integrated approach ensures that scorecards - and therefore performance management - are incorporated in the day-to-day running of the organisation.</li>\n	<li>Our process includes vertical and horizontal alignment, thereby addressing business processes and areas such as value chain performance that are often poorly managed in organisations.</li>\n	<li>Our offering enables an organisation to seamlessly execute its strategy, align teams and individuals and achieve engagement and buy-in.</li>\n	<li>Our approach is based on OIM''s proven performance improvement methodology and its basic performance elements, being clear purpose and direction, alignment and focus, effective leadership, business process/system integration and "knowing the score" through continuous performance measurement and improvement.</li>\n	<li>We enable an organisation to develop and implement team performance scorecards that are managed using OIM''s employee engagement methodology, INVOCOM®.</li>\n</ul>', 'Scorecards', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '697-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-10-18 14:22:13', '2013-10-18 12:22:13', '', 697, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/news/uncategorized/697-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(710, 3, '2013-10-18 14:24:59', '2013-10-18 12:24:59', 'Scorecards play a crucial role in organisational, team and individual performance management. They are used to translate strategic priorities to all organisational levels to establish overall alignment and a collective focus on the right goals and targets.\r\n\r\nUsing a structured approach, OIM''s scorecard development process aligns functional and team performance to the business strategy and standard operational areas. We clearly define goals and targets and cascade them throughout the business to accurately reflect level and content of work. This ensures that all functions add value to the business based on a common understanding of the organisational goals.\r\n\r\nWe also train staff in the use of scorecards and the contracting of performance.\r\n<h2>OUR OFFERING</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Consultation and scorecard design:</strong> Managing and facilitating the scorecard process. This includes reaching agreement on design principles, templates, roll-out method and timelines. An inclusive approach is adopted when designing the scorecards to generate a sense of ownership and buy-in among line managers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Training:</strong> Equipping leaders with the necessary skills to design and manage scorecards and agree on a performance contract with teams/individuals.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Toolkit:</strong> Designing and customising a toolkit for ease of implementation, eg templates and user guides.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>The link with strategy, operational goals and individual performance</strong>\r\n\r\nScorecards are the tool that links strategy with operational goals as well as team and individual performance. OIM has the expertise to assist clients with strategic planning, developing operational scorecards, setting up teams to manage their <a title="Employee engagement (INVOCOMS)" href="http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/products-services/people-management/employee-engagement-invocoms/">own performance</a> and <a title="Individual Performance Management" href="http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/products-services/people-management/talent-management/individual-performance-management/">individual performance</a>, allowing for a seamless integration of the scorecard process with performance.\r\n<h2>THE OIM DIFFERENCE</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OIM''s integrated approach ensures that scorecards - and therefore performance management - are incorporated in the day-to-day running of the organisation.</li>\r\n	<li>Our process includes vertical and horizontal alignment, thereby addressing business processes and areas such as value chain performance that are often poorly managed in organisations.</li>\r\n	<li>Our offering enables an organisation to seamlessly execute its strategy, align teams and individuals and achieve engagement and buy-in.</li>\r\n	<li>Our approach is based on OIM''s proven performance improvement methodology and its basic performance elements, being clear purpose and direction, alignment and focus, effective leadership, business process/system integration and "knowing the score" through continuous performance measurement and improvement.</li>\r\n	<li>We enable an organisation to develop and implement team performance scorecards that are managed using OIM''s employee engagement methodology, INVOCOM®.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Scorecards', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '697-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-18 14:24:59', '2013-10-18 12:24:59', '', 697, 'http://192.168.1.15/~tyronestafford/oim/htdocs/news/uncategorized/697-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
